Hash Playground
===============

OVERVIEW
========
Hash Playground is an open-source Roblox project for experimenting with
hashes, checksums, and key derivation.

It started as a Roblox "game" and ended up closer to a desktop-style
utility app. The project is built with Luau and uses a GTK-inspired
interface for testing multiple algorithms in one place.

FEATURES
========
- MD5
- SHA-1
- SHA-256
- SHA-512
- BLAKE2b
- BLAKE3
- CRC-8
- CRC-16
- CRC-24
- CRC-32
- PBKDF2 with SHA-256 and SHA-512
- Custom and native backend support where available
- Full-screen utility-style interface built in code

PROJECT LAYOUT
==============
The project uses Rojo for source control and Studio sync.

- src/client/HashGUI.client.lua
  Main user interface and interaction logic

- src/shared/*.lua
  Hash, checksum, HMAC, and PBKDF2 modules

- default.project.json
  Rojo project mapping

DEVELOPMENT
===========
To work on the project locally:

  rojo serve

Then connect to the Rojo plugin in Roblox Studio and sync the project.

NOTES
=====
This project is mainly intended for testing, learning, and experimentation.

It is not meant to be a security product, password manager, or production
cryptography toolkit. It is a playground for exploring how these algorithms
behave inside Roblox and Luau.

F.A.Q.
======
Q: Is this a game?
A: Technically yes. Spiritually, it is a cryptographic utility wearing a
   Roblox nametag.

Q: Why does a Roblox project have this many hash functions?
A: It got out of hand in a very specific and enjoyable direction.

Q: Why are there both custom and native backends?
A: Because writing the algorithms was fun, and comparing them is even better.

Q: Why PBKDF2?
A: Because once hashes and HMAC showed up, key derivation was only a matter
   of time.

